TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeRouteView
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
             Combines the behaviors of <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Authorization.AuthorizeView" /> and <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.RouteView" />,
             so that it displays the page matching the specified route but only if the user
             is authorized to see it.
            
             Additionally, this component supplies a cascading parameter of type <see cref="T:System.Threading.Tasks.Task`1" />,
             which makes the user's current authentication state available to descendants.
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: NotAuthorized
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The content that will be displayed if the user is not authorized.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Authorizing
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The content that will be displayed while asynchronous authorization is in progress.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Resource
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The resource to which access is being controlled.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RouteData
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the route data. This determines the page that will be
            displayed and the parameter values that will be supplied to the page.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DefaultLayout
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the type of a layout to be used if the page does not
            declare any layout. If specified, the type must implement <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.IComponent" />
            and accept a parameter named <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.LayoutComponentBase.Body" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.DataManager
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            The DataManager is a data management component used for performing data operations in applications.
            It acts as an abstraction for using local data source - IEnumerable and remote data source - web services returning JSON or oData.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: HttpClientInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the HttpClient instance to be used  by DataManager.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Use HttpClientInstance property to inject named HttpClient into DataManager.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Url
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the endpoint URL. DataManager requests this URL when data is needed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: AdaptorInstance
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the custom adaptor class type. DataManager uses this type value to instantiate custom adaptor class.
            </summary>
            <remarks>DataManager uses Activator.CreateInstance method to create custom adaptor instance.
            Injecting services into custom adaptor class, is not supported while using this approach.
            To inject and use services, provide custom adaptor as a Blazor component by extending DataAdaptor class.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Adaptor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the data adaptor to be used by DataManager.
            <list type="bullet">
            <item>
            <term>BlazorAdaptor</term>
            <description>Default. BlazorAdaptor is used to process Enumerable data. It contains methods to process the given collection based on the queries.</description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            OData Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData services.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>ODataV4Adaptor</term>
            <description>
            ODatav4 Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from OData v4 services
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>WebApiAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            WebApi Adaptor provies ability to consume and manipulate data from WebApi services.
            This adaptor is targeted to interact with Web API created using OData endpoint, it is extended from ODataAdaptor
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>UrlAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            URL Adaptor is used when you are required to interact with all kind of remote services to retrieve data.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>RemoteSaveAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            Remote Save Adaptor is used for binding JSON data.
            It interacts with remote services only for CRUD operations.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>CustomAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            CustomAdaptor specifies that own data query and manipulation logic has been provided using custom adaptor component
            extended from DataAdaptor class.
            </description>
            </item>
            <item>
            <term>JsonAdaptor</term>
            <description>
            JsonAdaptor is used to process JSON data at the client side. It contains methods to process the given JSON data based on the queries.
            </description>
            </item>
            </list>
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataAdaptor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Holds adaptor instance.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: InsertUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the insert URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Insert method is called, request will be made to InsertUrl.
            If InsertUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: RemoveUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the remove URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Remove method is called, request will be made to RemoveUrl.
            If RemoveUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: UpdateUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the update URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Update method is called, request will be made to UpdateUrl.
            If UpdateUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrudUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the CRUD URL.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When Insert, Remove or Update method is called, request will be made to CrudUrl.
            If CrudUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: BatchUrl
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the batch url.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Applicable for remote adaptors.
            When SaveChanges method is called, request will be made to BatchUrl.
            If BatchUrl is not provided, Url is used as fallback.</remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Json
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the IEnumerable collection. This data could be queried and manipulated.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Headers
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the key/value pair of headers.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Use Headers to add any custom headers to the request made by DataManager.
            Users can also send authentication bearer token using Headers property.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: Accept
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the accept type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Data
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the IEnumerale data.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: TimeTillExpiration
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the time limit to clear the cached data.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CachingPageSize
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the caching page size.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableCaching
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables data caching.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: RequestType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the request type for sending data fetching.
            </summary>
            <exclude />

BoundAttributes.Name: Key
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the primary key value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrossDomain
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When true, then indicates that the request is a cross-domain request.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Jsonp
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the jsonp request.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DataType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the data type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Offline
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables offline mode in datamanager.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Applicable for remote data source. If offline is true then initial request will be made to fetch
            data. Further actions will be handled at the in-memory data and no more request will be made to the service.
            Cached data is stored in the JSON property.
            </remarks>

            Sepcifies requires format.
            </summary>

            </summary>
            <exclude />

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery
TagHelpers.Documentation: The Blazor Media Query component allows developers to create responsive layouts. The component tracks changes in the browser size and notifies when the browser size matches the specified media query. The class is used to store information about each media query breakpoint, including the Breakpoint name and the MediaQuery itself. The property returns the Breakpoint of the MediaBreakpoint in the MediaBreakpoints collection that matches the current browser size. This allows developers to easily create responsive layouts that adapt to different screen sizes and device types. Loading... } else { @if(activeBreakpoint == "Small") { } else { } } @code { private string activeBreakpoint; } ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: ActiveBreakpoint
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.Breakpoint" /> of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.MediaQuery" /> in <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.MediaBreakpoints" /> collection that matches with the current browser size.
            Based on the <c>ActiveBreakpoint</c>, developers can easily create responsive layouts that adapt to different screen sizes and device types.
            </summary>
            <value>
            A string value that represents the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.Breakpoint" /> of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.MediaQuery" /> in <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.MediaBreakpoints" /> collection that matches with the browser size.
            The default value is <c>null</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: MediaBreakpoints
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the collection of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint" /> that contains the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.Breakpoint" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.MediaQuery" />.
            <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.ActiveBreakpoint" /> is set when a <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.MediaQuery" /> matches with the current browser size from this collection.
            </summary>
            <value>
            A collection of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint" /> that contains the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.Breakpoint" /> and <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint.MediaQuery" />.
            The defaul value is empty collection.
            </value>
            <remarks>
            If <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.MediaBreakpoints" /> is not specified, <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery" /> will use built-in collection of <see cref="T:Syncfusion.Blazor.MediaBreakpoint" /> that contains <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.Small" />, <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.Medium" /> and <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.SfMediaQuery.Large" /> media queries.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Annotation is a user defined HTML element that can be placed on chart
            We can use annotations to pile up the visual elegance of the chart.
            Specifies the customization of annotation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets and sets the content of the UI element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ContentTemplate
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets and sets the Template content of this annotation.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Content
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Content of the annotation, which accepts the id of the custom element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CoordinateUnits
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the coordinate units of the annotation. They are
            Pixel - Annotation renders based on x and y pixel value.
            Point - Annotation renders based on x and y axis value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Description
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Information about annotation for assistive technology.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Region
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the regions of the annotation. They are
            Chart - Annotation renders based on chart coordinates.
            Series - Annotation renders based on series coordinates.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: X
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if set coordinateUnit as `Pixel` X specifies the axis value
            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Y
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if set coordinateUnit as `Pixel` Y specifies the axis value
            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Legend is used to help readers understand the plotted data.
            The chart legend shows information about the datasets that are appearing on the chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ChildContent
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Sets and gets the content of the UI element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Alignment
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Legend in chart can be aligned as follows:
             Near: Aligns the legend to the left of the chart.
             Center: Aligns the legend to the center of the chart.
             Far: Aligns the legend to the right of the chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Background
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the legend that accepts value in hex and rgba as a valid CSS color string.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Border
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options to customize the border of the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Description
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Description for legends.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Height
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The height of the legend in pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Location
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the location of the legend, relative to the chart.
            If x is 20, legend moves by 20 pixels to the right of the chart. It requires the `Position` to be `Custom`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Margin
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Options to customize left, right, top and bottom margins of the chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Opacity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Opacity of the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Padding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Option to customize the padding around legend items.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ItemPadding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Option to customize the padding between legend items.
            Applicable for top and bottom legend position only.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Position of the legend in the chart are,
            Auto: Places the legend based on area type.
            Top: Displays the legend at the top of the chart.
            Left: Displays the legend at the left of the chart.
            Bottom: Displays the legend at the bottom of the chart.
            Right: Displays the legend at the right of the chart.
            Custom: Displays the legend  based on the given x and y value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShapeHeight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Shape height of the legend in pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShapePadding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Padding between the legend shape and text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShapeWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Shape width of the legend in pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TabIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            TabIndex legendItem for the legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextStyle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options to customize the legend text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToggleVisibility
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, series' visibility collapses based on the legend visibility.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableHighlight
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enabling highlight for legend.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, legend will be visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Width
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The width of the legend in pixels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsInversed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to inverse legend item content (image and text).
            </summary>
            <value> 
            true if the legend should be inversed; otherwise, false. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Reverse
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets whether to reverse the legend items order.
            </summary>
            <value> 
            true if the legend should be reverse; otherwise, false. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextOverflow
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
             Gets and sets the text overflow behavior to employ when the individual legend text overflowing the legend bounds or 
             <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings.MaximumLabelWidth"> MaximumLabelWidth </see> 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
             One of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings.TextOverflow" /> enumeration.The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.LabelOverflow.Ellipse" /> 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextWrap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
             Gets and sets the text wrap behavior to employ when the individual legend text overflowing the legend bounds or <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings.MaximumLabelWidth"> MaximumLabelWidth </see> 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
             One of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings.TextWrap" /> enumeration. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.TextWrap.Normal" /> 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaximumLabelWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
             Gets and sets the maximum width of the individual legend item after which they get trimmed, wrapped or clipped. 
            </summary> 
            <value> 
             Specifies the maximum width for the legend text. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: PageSettings
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
            Gets and sets the option to customize the legend arrow size and font styles for paging number texts.
            </summary>
            <value>
            Accept the instance of the <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationChartLegendSettings.PageSettings" /> value that specifies the customization options for paging elements in the legend.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Defines the distance between the segments of a funnel/pyramid series. The range will be from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            AccumulationSeries y values less than groupMode are combined into single slice named others.

            </summary>

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: InnerRadius
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            When the innerRadius value is greater than 0 percentage, a donut will appear in pie series. It takes values only in percentage.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LegendShape
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The shape of the legend. Each series has its own legend shape. They are
            Circle - Renders a circle.
            Rectangle - Renders a rectangle.
            Triangle - Renders a triangle.
            Diamond - Renders a diamond.
            Cross - Renders a cross.
            HorizontalLine - Renders a horizontalLine.
            VerticalLine - Renders a verticalLine.
            Pentagon - Renders a pentagon.
            InvertedTriangle - Renders a invertedTriangle.
            SeriesType -Render a legend shape based on series type.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Angle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Border
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Option for customizing the border lines.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ConnectorStyle
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options for customize the connector line in series.
            This property is applicable for Pie, Funnel and Pyramid series.
            The default connector length for Pie series is '4%'. For other series, it is null.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableRotation
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables rotation for data label.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Fill
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The background color of the data label, which accepts value in hex, rgba as a valid CSS color string.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Font
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Option for customizing the data label text.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The DataSource field which contains the data label value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Format
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             Gets and sets the data label format that accepts any global string format like 'C', 'P', 'N1', etc.
             It also accepts placeholder like '{value}°C' in which value represent the data label, for example, 20°C. 
            </summary>
            <value>
             Specifies the format for the data label. The default value is <c>null</c>.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: Position
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of data label. They are.
            Outside - Places label outside the point.
            Inside - Places label inside the point.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: MaxWidth
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
             Gets and sets the maximum width of the individual datalabel item after which they get trimmed, wrapped.  
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextOverflow
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>  
             Gets and sets the text overflow behavior to employ when the individual datalabel text overflowing the point segment or slice or <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationDataLabelSettings.MaxWidth"> MaxWidth </see> 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: TextWrap
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary> 
             Gets and sets the text wrap behavior to employ when the individual datalabel text overflowing the point segment or slice or <see cref="P:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.AccumulationDataLabelSettings.MaxWidth"> MaxWidth </see> 
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Rx
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The roundedCornerX for the data label. It requires `Border` values not to be null.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Ry
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The roundedCornerY for the data label. It requires `Border` values not to be null.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Template
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Custom template to format the data label content. Use ${point.x} and ${point.y} as a placeholder
            text to display the corresponding data point.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, data label for series gets render.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ShowZero
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set true, datalabels will be visible for zero points.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Context
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Specifies the parameter name for all child content expressions.

            </summary>

             Pixel - Annotation renders based on x and y pixel value.
             Point - Annotation renders based on x and y axis value.

<summary>
            Information about annotation for assistive technology.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Region
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>

             Chart - Annotation renders based on chart coordinates.
             Series - Annotation renders based on series coordinates.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: X
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if set coordinateUnit as `Pixel` X specifies the axis value
            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: XAxisName
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of horizontal axis associated with the annotation.
            It requires `Axes` of chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Y
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            if set coordinateUnit as `Pixel` Y specifies the axis value
            else is specifies pixel or percentage of coordinate.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: YAxisName
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The name of vertical axis associated with the annotation.
            It requires `Axes` of chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsIndexed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies indexed category  axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IsInversed
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            It specifies whether the axis to be rendered in inversed manner or not.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Name
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Unique identifier of an axis.
            To associate an axis with the series, set this name to the xAxisName/yAxisName properties of the series.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: OpposedPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, the axis will render at the opposite side of its default position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Title
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the title of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ValueType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the type of data the axis is handling.
            Double:  Renders a numeric axis.
            DateTime: Renders a dateTime axis.
            Category: Renders a category axis.
            Logarithmic: Renders a log axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Visible
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, axis label will be visible.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Coefficient
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The polar radar radius position.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ColumnIndex
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the index of the column where the axis is associated,
            when the chart area is divided into multiple plot areas by using `Columns`.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrossesAt
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the value at which the axis line has to be intersect with the vertical axis or vice versa.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: CrossesInAxis
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies axis name with which the axis line has to be crossed.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Description
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Description for axis and its element.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: DesiredIntervals
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            With this property, you can request axis to calculate intervals approximately equal to your specified interval.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EdgeLabelPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the position of labels at the edge of the axis.They are,
             None: No action will be performed.
             Hide: Edge label will be hidden.
             Shift: Shifts the edge labels.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableAutoIntervalOnZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, axis interval will be calculated automatically with respect to the zoomed range.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableScrollbarOnZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Enables the scrollbar for zooming.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableTrim
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the Trim property for an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: IntervalType
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the types like `Years`, `Months`, `Days`, `Hours`, `Minutes`, `Seconds` in date time axis.They are,
            Auto: Defines the interval of the axis based on data.
            Years: Defines the interval of the axis in years.
            Months: Defines the interval of the axis in months.
            Days: Defines the interval of the axis in days.
            Hours: Defines the interval of the axis in hours.
            Minutes: Defines the interval of the axis in minutes.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Interval
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the interval for an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Minimum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the minimum range of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPlacement
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the placement of a label for category axis. They are,
            betweenTicks: Renders the label between the ticks.
            onTicks: Renders the label on the ticks.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Maximum
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the maximum range of an axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZoomFactor
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The axis is scaled by this factor. When zoomFactor is 0.5, the chart is scaled by 200% along this axis. Value ranges from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ZoomPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Position of the zoomed axis. Value ranges from 0 to 1.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelFormat
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Used to format the axis label that accepts any global string format like 'C', 'n1', 'P' etc.
            It also accepts placeholder like '{value}°C' in which value represent the axis label, e.g, 20°C.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelIntersectAction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the actions like `None`, `Hide`, `Trim`, `Wrap`, `MultipleRows`, `Rotate45`, and `Rotate90`
            when the axis labels intersect with each other.They are,
            None: Shows all the labels.
            Hide: Hides the label when it intersects.
            Trim: Trim the label when it intersects.
            Wrap: Wrap the label when it intersects.
            MultipleRows: Shows the label in MultipleRows when it intersects.
            Rotate45: Rotates the label to 45 degree when it intersects.
            Rotate90: Rotates the label to 90 degree when it intersects.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPadding
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the labelPadding from axis.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: LabelPosition
BoundAttributes.Documentation:

TagHelpers.Documentation: Configures the sorting option for the chart. This example shows how to sort a chart by the "Y" property in asscending order. … ]]>

BoundAttributes.Name: Direction
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Get and set the sorting direction for the chart data. The available direction are,
            <list type="bullet">
            <item> 
            <term>Ascending</term> 
            <description> Sort from smallest to largest. For example, from A to Z.</description>
            </item> 
            <item> 
            <term>Descending</term>
            <description> Sort from largest to smallest. For example, from Z to A.</description> 
            </item> 
            </list>
            </summary> 
            <value>
            Sorts the chart in ascending order.  
            The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Data.ListSortDirection.Ascending" />.
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: PropertyName
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets or sets the property name being used as the sorting criteria. 
            </summary>
            <value>
            Specifies property name for the sorting. The default value is <c>null</c>. 
            </value>
            <remarks> 
            PropertyName property takes x, y, high, low, open, close and size fields of the chart data source.
            </remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.ChartZoomSettings
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            Options to customize the zoom settings of the chart.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableDeferredZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
             If set to true, zooming will be performed on mouse up. It requires `EnableSelectionZooming` to be true.
            
             </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableMouseWheelZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, chart can be zoomed by using mouse wheel.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePan
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether chart needs to be panned by default.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnablePinchZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If to true, chart can be pinched to zoom in / zoom out.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableScrollbar
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether axis needs to have scrollbar.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: EnableSelectionZooming
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If set to true, chart can be zoomed by a rectangular selecting region on the plot area.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: Mode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies whether to allow zooming vertically or horizontally or in both ways. They are,
            x,y: Chart can be zoomed both vertically and horizontally.
            x: Chart can be zoomed horizontally.
            y: Chart can be zoomed  vertically.
            It requires `EnableSelectionZooming` to be true.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolbarDisplayMode
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Gets and sets the zooming toolbar visibility for the chart. The available modes are,
            OnDemand: The zooming toolbar items are only visible while the chart has zoomed.
            Always: The zooming toolbar items are always visible even though the chart has not zoomed.
            None: The zooming toolbar items will not be visible even though the chart is zoomed.
            </summary>
            <value>
            Customize the zooming toolbar items visibility. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.ToolbarMode.OnDemand" />
            </value>

BoundAttributes.Name: ToolbarItems
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Specifies the toolkit options for the zooming as follows:
            Zoom
            ZoomIn
            ZoomOut
            Pan
            Reset.
            </summary>

            OnDemand: The zooming toolbar items are only visible while the chart has zoomed.
            Always: The zooming toolbar items are always visible even though the chart has not zoomed.
            None: The zooming toolbar items will not be visible even though the chart is zoomed.
            </summary>
            <value>
            Customize the zooming toolbar items visibility. The default value is <see cref="F:Syncfusion.Blazor.Charts.ToolbarMode.OnDemand" />
            </value>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting <script> elements that supports fallback src paths.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            The tag helper won't process for cases with just the 'src' attribute.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Address of the external script to use.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            Passed through to the generated HTML in all cases.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to load.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from loading.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.SrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The URL of a Script tag to fallback to in the case the primary one fails.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-suppress-fallback-integrity
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Boolean value that determines if an integrity hash will be compared with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrc" /> value.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-append-version
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            Value indicating if file version should be appended to src urls.
            </summary>
            <remarks>
            A query string "v" with the encoded content of the file is added.
            </remarks>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-include
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to fallback to in the case the
            primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-src-exclude
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            A comma separated list of globbed file patterns of JavaScript scripts to exclude from the fallback list, in
            the case the primary one fails.
            The glob patterns are assessed relative to the application's 'webroot' setting.
            Must be used in conjunction with <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ScriptTagHelper.FallbackSrcInclude" />.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-fallback-test
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            The script method defined in the primary script to use for the fallback test.
            </summary>

            attribute.
            </summary>

BoundAttributes.Name: asp-validation-summary
BoundAttributes.Documentation:
<summary>
            If <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.All" /> or <see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.ModelOnly" />, appends a validation
            summary. Otherwise (<see cref="F:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Rendering.ValidationSummary.None" />, the default), this tag helper does nothing.
            </summary>
            <exception cref="T:System.ArgumentException">
            Thrown if setter is called with an undefined <see cref="P:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.TagHelpers.ValidationSummaryTagHelper.ValidationSummary" /> value e.g.
            <c>(ValidationSummary)23</c>.
            </exception>

TagHelpers.Name: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.TagHelpers.UrlResolutionTagHelper
TagHelpers.Documentation:
<summary>
            <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" /> implementation targeting elements containing attributes with URL expected values.
            </summary>
            <remarks>Resolves URLs starting with '~/' (relative to the application's 'webroot' setting) that are not
            targeted by other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s. Runs prior to other <see cref="T:Microsoft.AspNetCore.Razor.TagHelpers.ITagHelper" />s to ensure
            application-relative URLs are resolved.</remarks>

TagHelpers.Name: Bind
TagHelpers.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributes.Name: @bind-...
BoundAttributes.Documentation: Binds the provided expression to an attribute and a change event, based on the naming of the bind attribute. For example: @bind-value="..." and @bind-value:event="onchange" will assign the current value of the expression to the 'value' attribute, and assign a delegate that attempts to set the value to the 'onchange' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: format
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies a format to convert the value specified by the corresponding bind attribute. For example: @bind-value:format="..." will apply a format string to the value specified in @bind-value="...". The format string can currently only be used with expressions of type DateTime.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: event
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the event handler name to attach for change notifications for the value provided by the '@bind-...' attribute.

BoundAttributeParameters.Name: culture
BoundAttributeParameters.Documentation: Specifies the culture to use for conversions.
